Independent investigators called into Royal Oldham after deaths of four babies and two mothers in eight months . 
  Lisa Parkisson died at Oldham Royal 48 hours after giving birth in April . 
  Thomas Beaty died at the same hospital in June after doctors pushed him back into the womb during birth . 
  North Manchester General also had deaths of three babies and one mother . 
  Independent investigators found failings in care and hospital leadership at the two hospitals . 
 